</TABLE>
</DIV>
</EFX_NAME_AND_TITLE>
</EFX_BUSINESS>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item&nbsp;1A.&nbsp;&nbsp;RISK FACTORS
</FONT>
<A NAME="CHKE-20160130X10K_HTM_ITEM1ARISKFACTORS_16153">
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The occurrence of any of the risks and uncertainties and other factors described below and elsewhere in this Annual Report and the other documents we file with the SEC could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition, results of operations and share price and could also cause our future business, financial condition and results of operations to differ materially from our historical results and the results contemplated by any forward-looking statements we may make herein, in any other document we file with the SEC, or in any press release or other written or oral statement we may make. You should carefully consider all of these risks and the other information in this Annual Report and the other documents we file with the SEC before making any investment decision with respect to our common stock. The risks described below and elsewhere in this Annual Report are not the only ones we face. Additional risks we are not presently aware of or that we currently believe are immaterial may also impair our financial condition and business operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Risks Related to Our Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our business is subject to intense competition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Royalties paid to us under our licensing agreements are generally based on a percentage of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019; net sales of licensed products.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Additionally, franchisees of our Flip Flop Shops brand pay us a percentage of their net sales. Merchandise bearing our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Cherokee, Carole Little
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, Sideout,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Liz Lange, Completely Me by Liz Lange, Hawk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Tony Hawk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and Everyday California
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	brands, all of which are manufactured and sold by both domestic and international wholesalers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage15"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#CHKE-20160130X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and retail licensees,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as well as merchandise sold by Flip Flop Shops retail shops,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	are subject to extensive competition by numerous domestic and foreign companies. Such competitors with respect to the Cherokee brand include Polo Ralph Lauren, Tommy Hilfiger, Liz Claiborne, and private label brands (developed by retailers) such as Faded Glory, Arizona, Merona, and Route 66. Factors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shape the competitive environment include quality of garment construction and design, brand name, style and color selection, price, fashion and other trends, avenue of purchase (including in stores and online), and the manufacturer&#x2019;s ability to respond quickly to the retailer on a national basis. In recognition of what we believe is an increasing trend toward consolidation of retailers, our business plan in the United States focuses on creating strategic alliances with major retailers for their sale of products bearing our brands through the licensing of our trademarks directly to retailers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and, to a lesser extent, entering into franchise relationships with Flip Flop Shops retail store owners and engaging wholesalers to manufacture products bearing our brands and sell these products to retailers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Therefore, our degree of success is dependent on the strength of our brands, consumer acceptance of and desire for our brands, our licensees&#x2019; ability to design, manufacture and sell products bearing our brands and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our franchisees&#x2019; ability to sell products bearing our or third-party brands, and the ability of our licensees and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to respond to ever
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	changing consumer demands. Failures with respect to any of these factors could have a material adverse effect on our business prospects, financial condition, results of operations and liquidity. We cannot control the level of consumer acceptance of our brands and changing preferences and trends may lead customers to purchase other products. Further, we cannot control the level of resources that our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	commit to supporting our brands, and our licensees may choose to support
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products bearing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	other brands to the detriment of our brands because our agreements generally do not prevent our licensees from licensing from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	selling products of,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our competitors. In addition, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	compete
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with other companies owning established trademarks, which have entered into, and could continue to enter into, similar arrangements with retailers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and wholesale manufacturers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the U.S. and internationally, including with our existing retail
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and wholesale
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	partners, thereby competing with us for consumer attention
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	limited floor and rack space in the same stores in which our branded products are sold
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and time and resources of wholesale licensees that manufacture our products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We are subject to risks related to the retail business that are applicable to our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	and franchisees.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	There are numerous risks and other factors applicable to the businesses of retailers (including our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) that can impact the sale of products that bear our brands
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and, with respect to our franchisees, the sale of products bearing other brands from which we generate revenues
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Any decline in sales by one or more of our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or franchisees could
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	adversely affect our revenues.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Factors that may adversely affect our licensees and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	franchisees and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	their sales of products include the following, among others: (i)&nbsp;weather, environmental or other conditions that may impact consumer shopping activity in retail stores; (ii)&nbsp;consumer preferences regarding fashion trends and styles, which can be region
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	dependent and subject to rapid and significant fluctuations; (iii)&nbsp;consumer preferences regarding where to shop; (iv)&nbsp;the growth of online shopping and the ability of our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to market and sell products through these avenues; (v)&nbsp;changes in the availability or cost of capital in light of the financial condition and capital requirements of our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	; (vi)&nbsp;shifts in the seasonality of shopping patterns; (vii)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	fluctuating
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	retail prices; (viii)&nbsp;labor strikes or other interruptions that impact supply chains and transport vendors (ix)&nbsp;the impact of excess retail capacity; (x)&nbsp;changes in the cost of accepting various payment methods and changes in the rate of utilization of these payment methods; (xi)&nbsp;material acquisitions or dispositions; (xii)&nbsp;investments in new business strategies; (xiii)&nbsp;the success or failure of significant new business ventures or technologies; (xiv)&nbsp;actions taken or omitted to be taken by legislative, regulatory, judicial and other governmental authorities and officials; (xv)&nbsp;security breaches; (xvi)&nbsp;natural disasters, the outbreak of war, acts of terrorism or other significant national or international events; and (xvii)&nbsp;the other risks discussed in this Item&nbsp;1A.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We rely on the accuracy of our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x2019;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x2019; retail sales reports for reporting and collecting our revenues, and if these reports are untimely or incorrect, our revenues could be delayed or inaccurately reported
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	or collected.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Most of our revenues are generated from retailers who license our brands
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	manufacture and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sell
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products bearing our brands in their stores and on their websites
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. In addition, we have a number of franchise agreements with franchisees of the Flip Flop Shops brand and we have arrangements with several wholesalers who license our brands to manufacture products bearing our brands and sell these products to retailers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Under our existing agreements, these licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	pay us fees based in part on the value of products sold. We rely on our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	13
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage16"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#CHKE-20160130X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to accurately report the retail sales in collecting our license
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	fees, preparing our financial reports, projections and budgets, and directing our sales and marketing efforts. All of our license
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	agreements permit us to audit our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. If any of our licensee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or franchisee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	reports understate the retail sales of products they sell, we may not collect and recognize revenues to which we are entitled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on a timely basis or at all
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or may endure significant expense to obtain compliance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our business is dependent on the success of our Direct to Retail licensing model
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	, as well as our other licensing and franchising models.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Although we recently commenced franchise operations with our acquisition of the Flip Flop Shops brand and we intend to grow this business in the future and we also recently entered into several new licensing arrangements with wholesalers and may seek to enter into additional wholesale arrangements in the future, we continue to be focused on our Direct to Retail licensees.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In Direct to Retail licensing, we grant retailers a license to use our trademarks on certain categories of merchandise. In many cases, the licensee is responsible for designing and manufacturing the merchandise, although we typically collaborate with our licensees&#x2019; product development staff and merchandisers on design direction, packaging, marketing, and other aspects pertaining to products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	bearing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our trademarks. Over the past two decades, the Direct to Retail licensing model has become more widely accepted by many retailers worldwide, and our business plan is still based on the continued success of this model with our current licensees and with new retailers we may solicit to license our brands in new territories and additional product categories as we seek to expand our business. Although we believe there is an increasing trend towards consolidation of retailers, which could support the growth of our Direct to Retail licensing model, this belief may turn out to be wrong. If our current or potential future retail licensees do not perceive our Direct to Retail licensing model to be advantageous to them, then they may move away from this model and instead embrace alternatives, such as purchasing from wholesalers or manufacturing private label products. Such a change in perception could occur for a variety of reasons, including reasons based on retailers&#x2019; beliefs or expectations that do not turn out to be accurate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Further, even though our pursuits of wholesale and franchise models may diversify our sources of revenue in the event that our expectations regarding Direct to Retail licensing trends do not prove to be accurate, these pursuits could themselves be unsuccessful and could divert management&#x2019;s attention and other resources, including time and capital, from our Direct to Retail licensing strategy. As a result, our future success depends in part on our ability to successfully manage these multiple licensing avenues.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	If our Direct to Retail licensing model ceases to be attractive to retailers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or we are unable to manage our wholesale and franchise arrangements together with our Direct to Retail licensing model
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, then we would be unable to continue to pursue our business plan and our financial condition and prospects would be harmed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our business is largely dependent on royalties from Target
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	, which has notified us that it will not renew its current relationship with us for the Cherokee brand.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Royalty revenues from our Cherokee brand at Target accounted for greater than 40% of our consolidated revenues during each of Fiscal 2016, Fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015 and Fiscal 2014. In September 2015, Target informed us that it would not renew its license agreement covering sales of Cherokee branded products in the U.S., which expires at the end of its current term on January&nbsp;31, 2017 for most Cherokee branded products. The license agreement with Target, including the existing royalty obligations, will remain in effect and continue to generate revenues to us in Fiscal 2017 until its expiration. Our license agreement with Target covering sales of Cherokee branded products in the school uniforms category will expire at the end of its current term on January 31, 2018, and will continue to generate revenues to us until its expiration. If
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Target were to reduce its sales of Cherokee branded products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	prior to expiration of its license
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, even if Target continues to pay the minimum annual
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	royalties
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	required under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	license agreement with Target
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, any increased revenues we may receive from other licensees or franchisees may not be sufficient to offset such a reduction in royalty revenues from Target
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Replacing the royalty payments received from Target is be a significant challenge
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and we might not be successful in doing so
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. If we are not successful in replacing the Target royalty payments with equal or greater payments from other partners
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the termination of this license agreement, which currently extends through January&nbsp;31,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2017 could
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	adverse effect upon our revenues and cash flow. In addition, in September 2012 we expanded our relationship with Target
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	when we assumed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	an additional license agreement with Target for the Liz Lange brand, which we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	do not expect to be affected by the non-renewal of our agreements with Target covering Cherokee branded products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	14
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage17"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<A HREF="#CHKE-20160130X10K_HTM_TOC">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We acquired the Liz Lange brand in part based upon our expectation that revenues from Target for this brand
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	would
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	grow in future periods, although such revenue growth may never occur. As a result of our reliance on Target
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	at least through Fiscal 2017,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our continued success is dependent on various factors affecting Target&#x2019;s business, including, for example, perceptions of Target by consumers in the United States. For example, we believe that sales of Cherokee branded products at Target in the United States after the fourth quarter of Fiscal 2014 were adversely impacted following Target&#x2019;s announcement of unauthorized access to payment card data in U.S. stores.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenues from our Hawk and Tony Hawk brands depend on Kohl&#x2019;s.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In January 2014, we acquired the Hawk and Tony Hawk brands. Concurrently with this acquisition, we entered into a retail license agreement with Kohl&#x2019;s, pursuant to which Kohl&#x2019;s is granted the exclusive right to sell Tony Hawk and Hawk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	branded apparel and related products in the United States. We agreed to this exclusive license in part based upon our expectation that revenues from Kohl&#x2019;s for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	these
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	brands will grow in future periods, although this expectation may turn out to be wrong and such revenue growth may never occur beyond the $4.8&nbsp;million minimum annual royalty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	payment required
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	under the license agreement.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The failure of our licensees to sell products bearing our brands or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	our franchisees to sell products that generate royalties to us,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	to pay us royalties for such products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	or to renew their license or franchise agreements with us
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	could result in a decline in our results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our revenues are dependent on royalty payments made to us under our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	license and franchise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	agreements. Although the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	license
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	agreements for our brands in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	many
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	cases provide for guaranteed minimum royalty payments to us, the failure of our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to satisfy their obligations under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	their
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	agreements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with us, their decision to not renew their agreements with us
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or their inability to grow or maintain their businesses could cause our revenues to suffer. Further, while we are substantially dependent on our relationships with Target and Kohl&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and expect to continue to be at least through Fiscal 2017 when our agreement with Target for the Cherokee brand will expire
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the concurrent failure by several of our other material licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to meet their financial obligations to us
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or to renew their respective license or franchise agreements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	could materially and adversely impact our results of operation and our financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our franchise business exposes us to numerous risks.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In connection with our acquisition of the Flip Flop Shops brand in October 2015, we acquired, and became the franchisor under, a number of franchise agreements with franchisees of this brand. Many of these franchisees maintain one or more Flip Flop Shops retail stores located across the globe, including in the U.S., Canada, the Caribbean, the Middle East and South Africa. This new Flip Flop Shops franchise business exposes us to a variety of risks, including, among others, that: (i)&nbsp;we may not be able to find capable and experienced franchisees who can implement the Flip Flop Shops brand concept and strategies we believe are necessary for the future growth of this brand or sell merchandise and operate stores in a manner consistent with our standards and requirements, which could limit our revenues from this brand and diminish the image and reputation of this brand and our other brands; (ii)&nbsp;even if we are able to attract capable franchise owners, these franchisees may not be able to open new Flip Flop Shops retail stores in a timely manner, or manage and maintain them once opened, if they cannot secure desirable site locations, obtain adequate financing, construct and develop new store locations without delays and attract qualified operating personnel, which could slow the growth of this brand and reduce our franchise revenues; (iii)&nbsp;the third party brands that are sold at Flip Flop Shops stores could decline in popularity or decide to stop selling their merchandise at some or all of the Flip Flop Shops store locations, which could cause sales at these stores to decline; (iv) neighborhood or economic conditions or other demographic patterns where existing or new Flip Flop Shops stores are located could decline or otherwise change in a negative way, which could result in reduced sales by these store locations; and (v)&nbsp;our franchise business is subject to complex and varying franchise laws and regulations imposed by the U.S. federal, state and foreign jurisdictions in which we operate, &nbsp;and we may need to devote significant costs and resources in order to learn and comply with these laws and regulations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#CHKE-20160130X10K_HTM_TOC">

	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our wholesale licensing arrangements are subject to a number of risks.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In our wholesale licensing relationships, we license our brands to manufacturers that produce and import various categories of apparel, footwear, home products and accessories under our trademarks and sell the licensed products to retailers. We have some historical wholesale licensees with respect to some of our brands and we have recently entered into several new wholesale arrangements. In these arrangements, we have a limited ability to control the manufacturing process, access to raw materials, the timing for delivery of finished products, the quality of finished products or costs related to the manufacturing process. Any wholesale licensees we engage may not be able to produce finished products in quantities that are sufficient to meet retailer demand, in a timely manner or at all, which could result in an inability to generate revenue from any such products and loss of retailer confidence in our brands. On the other hand, wholesale licensees may produce inventory in excess of retailer and consumer demand, in which case over-supply may cause retail prices of products bearing our products to decline. Additionally, there may be delays in the manufacturing process over which we may have no control, including shortages of raw materials, labor disputes, backlogs or insufficient devotion of resources to the manufacture of products bearing our brands. Further, we compete with other brand owners for the time and resources of our wholesale licensees, which could curtail or limit our ability to engage new or maintain existing wholesale licensee partners on acceptable terms or at all. Interruptions in the supply of products bearing our brands to retailers or lapses in quality could adversely impact our financial condition. Further, the unplanned loss of any of our wholesale licensees could lead to inadequate market coverage for retail sales of products bearing our brands, create negative impressions of us and our brands with retailers and consumers and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;">
	add downward pressure on prices of products bearing our brands as a result of liquidating a former wholesaler&#x2019;s inventory of such products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our business may be negatively impacted by general economic conditions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our performance is subject to worldwide economic conditions and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	corresponding impact on levels of consumer spending, which may affect our licensees&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees&#x2019; retail
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales. It is difficult to predict future levels of consumer spending and any such predictions are inherently uncertain. Many factors affect the level of consumer spending in the apparel industries, including, among others, prevailing economic conditions, levels of employment, salaries and wage rates, energy costs, interest rates, the availability of consumer credit, taxation and consumer confidence in future economic conditions.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Further, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	worldwide apparel industry is heavily influenced by general economic cycles. Purchases of apparel, footwear and accessories tend to decline in periods of recession or uncertainty regarding future economic prospects, as disposable income typically declines. As a result,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	during periods of economic uncertainty, slowdown or recession,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the risks associated with our business are generally more acute . In addition to decreased consumer spending generally, these periods may be accompanied by decreased demand for, or additional downward pricing pressure on, the products carrying our brands. Accordingly, any prolonged economic slowdown
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a lengthy or severe recession
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or any other negative trend in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	either the U.S. or the global economy is likely to have a material adverse effect on our results of operations, financial condition and business prospects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We are subject to additional risks associated with our international licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	and franchisees.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	franchise our Flip Flop Shops brand and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	market and license our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	brands outside the United States. Many of our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	are located outside the United States. As a key component of our business strategy, we intend to expand our international sales as well as the support we provide our international licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. During Fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2016,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately 30% of our revenues were derived from our international licensees. We face numerous risks in doing business outside the United States, including: (i)&nbsp;unusual or burdensome foreign laws or regulatory requirements or unexpected changes to those laws or requirements; (ii)&nbsp;tariffs, trade protection measures, import or export licensing requirements, trade embargos, and other trade barriers; (iii)&nbsp;difficulties in attracting and retaining qualified personnel to manage foreign licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	; (iv)&nbsp;competition from foreign companies; (v)&nbsp;longer accounts receivable collection cycles and difficulties in collecting accounts receivable; (vi)&nbsp;less effective and less predictable protection and enforcement of our intellectual property; (vii)&nbsp;changes in the political or economic condition of a specific country or region, particularly in emerging markets; (viii)&nbsp;potentially adverse tax consequences; and (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ix
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	)&nbsp;cultural differences in the conduct of business. Any one or more of such factors could cause our future international sales to decline or could cause us to fail to execute on our business strategy involving international expansion. In addition, our business practices in international markets are subject to the requirements of the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act, any violation of which could subject us to significant fines, criminal sanctions and other penalties.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

	16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#CHKE-20160130X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Additionally, and because the majority of our international revenue is denominated in U.S. dollars, fluctuations in the value of the U.S. dollar relative to the foreign currencies of our international licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019; or franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2019; operations may negatively impact our royalty revenues. The main foreign currencies we encounter in our operations are the Mexican Peso, the EURO, the Great British Pound, the South African Rand, the Japanese Yen, the Chinese Yuan, and the Canadian Dollar. We do not currently engage in currency hedging activities to limit the risk of exchange rate fluctuations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our business and the success of our products could be harmed if we are unable to maintain the strength of our brands.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our success to date has been due in large part to the strength of our brands. If we are unable to timely and appropriately respond to changing consumer demand, the strength of our brands may be impaired. Even if we react appropriately to changes in consumer preferences, consumers may consider one or more of our brands to be outdated or associate one or more of our brands with styles that are no longer popular. In the past, many apparel companies have experienced periods of rapid growth in sales and earnings followed by periods of declining sales and losses. Our business may be similarly affected in the future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We are dependent on our intellectual property, and we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	may not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	be able to successfully protect our rights or we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	may
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	become involved in costly legal proceedings regarding our intellectual property.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We hold various trademarks for our brands, including Cherokee, Liz Lange, Completely Me by Liz Lange, Hawk, Tony Hawk,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Everyday California, Flip Flop Shops,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Sideout and Carole Little and others in connection with apparel, footwear, home and accessories. These trademarks are vital to the success and future growth of our business. These trademarks are registered with the United States Patent and Trademark Office and corresponding government agencies in numerous other countries and we also hold trademark applications for these brands in a number of other countries, although the laws of many countries may not protect our intellectual property rights to the same extent as the laws of the United States. These actions taken by us to establish and protect our trademarks and other proprietary rights might not prevent imitation of our products, infringement of our intellectual property rights by unauthorized parties or other challenges to our intellectual property ownership, or prevent the loss of licensing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or franchise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	revenue or other damages caused thereby. If any of these events occurs, our business prospects, financial condition, results of operations and liquidity could be materially harmed. In the future, we may be required to assert infringement claims against third parties, and one or more parties may assert infringement claims against us. Any resulting litigation could result in significant expense and divert the efforts of our management personnel whether or not such litigation is determined in our favor. Further, if any adverse ruling in any such matter occurs, any resulting limitations in our ability to market or license our brands could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may become involved in other litigation and administrative proceedings that may materially affect us.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	From time to time, we may become involved in various legal proceedings relating to matters incidental to the ordinary course of our business, including commercial, employment, class action and other litigation and claims, as well as governmental and other regulatory investigations, audits and proceedings. Such matters can be time
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consuming, divert management&#x2019;s attention and resources and cause us to incur significant expenses. Furthermore, because litigation is inherently unpredictable, the results of any of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	these actions or legal costs associated with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	these actions could have a material adverse effect on our business, results of operations or financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We are dependent on our key management personnel.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our success is highly dependent upon the continued services of our key executives
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, including, Henry Stupp, our Chief Executive Officer and a member of our Board or Directors, Howard Siegel, our President and Chief Operating Officer, Jason Boling, our Chief Financial Officer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and Brian Curin, the President of our subsidiary FFS Holdings, LLC, which manages our Flip Flop Shops franchise operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. We have a limited number of employees and Mr.&nbsp;Stupp&#x2019;s and our other executives&#x2019; leadership and experience in the apparel licensing industry
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and Mr.&nbsp;Curin&#x2019;s expertise in the franchising industry
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is important to the successful implementation of our business and marketing strategy. We do not carry key person life insurance covering any of our executives
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or other employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The loss of the services of Mr.&nbsp;Stupp or our other key executives
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	could have a material adverse effect on our business prospects, financial condition, results of operations and liquidity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#CHKE-20160130X10K_HTM_TOC">

	Table of Contents

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may encounter difficulties in connection with acquisitions or other strategic transactions and we may not realize the expected benefits from these transactions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We regularly evaluate opportunities to acquire or represent new brands. During the past three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years, we have consummated three such acquisitions: our acquisition of the Hawk and Tony Hawk signature apparel brands in January
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2014; our acquisition of the Everyday California Lifestyle brand in May&nbsp;2015; and our acquisition of the Flip Flop Shops brand in October 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We expect to continue to consider opportunities to acquire or make investments in other brands or to engage in other strategic transactions that could enhance our portfolio of products and services or expand the breadth of our markets. Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	experience
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	integrating
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	acquired assets and businesses
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is limited, and we may not be successful in realizing the expected benefits from an acquisition.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our future
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	success depends, in part, upon our ability to manage an expanded portfolio of brands, which could
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	involve significantly increased costs and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	pose substantial challenges for management. Acquisitions and other strategic transactions can involve numerous risks and potential difficulties, including, among others: (i)&nbsp;problems assimilating the brands; (ii)&nbsp;significant future charges relating the amortization of intangible assets; (iii)&nbsp;problems maintaining and enforcing standards, procedures, controls, policies and information systems; (iv)&nbsp;difficulty and cost in combining the operations and personnel of any acquired businesses with our operations and personnel, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	failure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to retain key employees of any acquired businesses; (v)&nbsp;unanticipated costs associated with an acquisition, including accounting and legal charges, capital expenditures, and transaction expenses; (vi)&nbsp;diversion of management&#x2019;s attention from our core business or our existing brand portfolio; (vii)&nbsp;adverse effects on existing business relationships with our partners; and (viii)&nbsp;risks associated with entering
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	new
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	markets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or new types of business arrangements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in which we have no or limited prior experience
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, such as, for instance, our acquisition of franchise agreements and entry into the franchising business upon our acquisition of the Flip Flop Shops brand in October 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Accordingly, our recent acquisitions as well as any future
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	transactions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that we pursue could have a material adverse effect on our business, results of operations, financial condition and prospects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, future acquisitions may also require us to obtain additional equity or debt financing, which may not be available when needed, on favorable terms or at all. If we finance future acquisitions or other strategic transactions by issuing equity or convertible debt securities, our existing stockholders would be diluted. If we finance future acquisitions or other strategic transactions by issuing debt, we may become over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-leveraged
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and our ability to operate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our business
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	may be restricted by the agreements governing the debt. In addition, we may experience or incur contingent liabilities, amortization expenses or write
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	offs of goodwill or trademarks in connection with such transactions. Any of these effects could harm our operating results or financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We have incurred a significant amount of indebtedness to pay the cash consideration for our recent acquisitions. Our level of indebtedness, and restrictions under such indebtedness, could adversely affect our operations and liquidity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	entered into a credit facility with JPMorgan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	September&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2012 and we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	increased the size of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	credit facility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2013, January 2014 and October 2015, in each case
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in connection with our acquisition of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	new brands or new rights relating to existing brands. Approximately $24&nbsp;million in principal amount was outstanding under our credit facility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as of January 30, 2016, and is evidenced by (i)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	term notes, which were issued on January&nbsp;31,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2013,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January&nbsp;10, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and October&nbsp;13, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the principal amounts of $16.6&nbsp;million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$19
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million and $6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million, respectively, and (ii)&nbsp;a revolving line of credit, pursuant to which we may borrow up to $2&nbsp;million in principal.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	All of our outstanding indebtedness owed under the credit facility is due in March 2017.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our indebtedness under the credit facility could adversely affect our operations and liquidity, by, among other things: making it more difficult for us to pay or refinance our debts as they become due during adverse economic and industry conditions because we may not have sufficient cash flows to make our scheduled debt payments; causing us to use a larger portion of our cash flow to fund interest and principal payments, thereby reducing the availability of cash to fund working capital, product development and capital expenditures and other business activities; making it more difficult for us to take advantage of significant business opportunities, such as acquisition opportunities or other strategic transactions, and to react to changes in market or industry conditions; and limiting our ability to borrow additional monies in the future to fund working capital, product development, capital expenditures
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, brand acquisitions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and other general corporate purposes.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We may seek to refinance all or a portion of this indebtedness before its maturity date. Any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	such refinancing would depend on the capital markets and our financial condition at the time, which could affect our ability to obtain attractive refinance terms when desired, or at all.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, the terms of our indebtedness contain various restrictions and covenants regarding the operation of our business, including covenants that require us to obtain JPMorgan&#x2019;s consent before we can: (i)&nbsp;incur additional indebtedness, (ii)&nbsp;consummate acquisitions, mergers or consolidations, (iii)&nbsp;issue any equity securities other than pursuant to our employee equity incentive plans or programs, or (iv)&nbsp;repurchase or redeem any outstanding shares of common stock or pay dividends or other distributions, other than stock dividends, to our stockholders. The credit facility also imposes financial covenants, including a minimum &#x201C;fixed charge coverage ratio&#x201D; of at least 1.2 to 1.0 and a limitation of our &#x201C;senior funded debt ratio&#x201D; to not exceed a ratio equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.00 to 1.00.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Further, as collateral for the credit facility, we granted a security interest in favor of JPMorgan in all of our assets (including trademarks), and our indebtedness is guaranteed by Cherokee&#x2019;s wholly owned subsidiaries.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Target&#x2019;s election in September 2015 to not renew the license agreement for the Cherokee brand in the U.S. triggered an event of default under the credit facility. However, we and JPMorgan entered into a forbearance agreement immediately after Target&#x2019;s non-renewal election and JPMorgan subsequently waived this event of default. If an event of default occurs under the credit facility that is not forborne, cured or waived in accordance with the terms of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the credit facility, JPMorgan has the right to terminate its obligations under the credit facility, accelerate the payment on any unpaid balance of the credit facility and exercise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	other rights
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	it may have,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	including foreclosing on our assets under the related security agreements. Our failure to comply with the terms of our indebtedness could
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a material adverse effect to our business, financial condition and liquidity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our future capital needs may be uncertain and we may need to raise additional funds in the future, and such funds may not be available
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	when needed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	on acceptable terms or at all.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our capital requirements in future periods may be uncertain and could depend upon many factors, including: acceptance of, and demand for, our brands; the costs of developing new brands; the extent to which we invest in new brands; the number and timing of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	acquisitions and other strategic transactions; the costs associated with our expansion, if any; and the costs of litigation and enforcement activities to defend our trademarks. In the future, we may need to raise additional funds, and such funds may not be available when needed, on favorable terms, or at all. Furthermore, if we issue equity or convertible debt securities to raise additional funds, our existing stockholders
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	would
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	experience dilution and the new equity or debt securities may have rights, preferences, and privileges senior to those of our existing stockholders, and if we incur additional debt to raise funds, we may become over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-leveraged
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and our ability to operate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our business
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	may be restricted by the agreements governing the debt. Moreover, we may incur substantial costs in pursuing future capital transactions, including investment banking fees, legal fees, accounting fees, printing and distribution expenses and other costs. If we cannot raise funds when needed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on acceptable terms or at all, we may not be able to develop or enhance our products and services, execute our business plan, take advantage of future opportunities, or respond to competitive pressures or unanticipated customer requirements. This may materially harm our business, results of operations and financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our strategic and marketing initiatives may not be successful.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In recent periods, we have invested significant funds and management time in furtherance of our global strategic and marketing initiatives, which are designed to strengthen our brands, assist our licensees in generating increased sales of products bearing our brands and build value for our stockholders over the long term. We expect to continue and, in some cases, expand such initiatives in future periods. While we are hopeful that our efforts in executing on these initiatives will expand our business and build stockholder value over the long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	term, we may not be successful in doing so and such initiatives may not result in the intended benefits. Any failure by us to execute on our strategic initiatives, or the failure of such initiatives to cause our revenues to grow, could have a materially adverse impact on our operating results and financial performance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We must successfully maintain and/or upgrade our information technology systems.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We rely on various information technology systems, including our Enterprise Resource Planning system, to manage our operations, which subjects us to inherent costs and risks associated with maintaining, upgrading, replacing and changing these systems, including impairment of our information technology, potential disruption of our internal control systems, substantial capital expenditures, demands on management time and delays or difficulties in upgrading
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	existing systems
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, transitioning to new systems or integrating new systems into our current systems.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our business and operations would suffer in the event of cybersecurity and other system failures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Despite the implementation of security measures, our internal computer systems and those of our licensees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and franchisees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	are vulnerable to damage from computer viruses, unauthorized access, natural disasters, terrorism, war and telecommunication and electrical failures. Although we have not experienced any such cybersecurity or system failure, accident or breach to date, some of our licensees, including Target, have experienced such events
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the past
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. If such an event were to occur to our internal systems, it could result in a material disruption of our operations, substantial costs to rectify or correct the failure, if possible, loss of or damage to our data or applications, inappropriate disclosure of confidential or proprietary information or the incurrence of other material liabilities. If such events were to occur to our licensees&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or franchisees&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	systems, our royalty revenues could be reduced or disrupted due to decreased sales of our branded products as a result of reputational damage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	diversion of costs and other resources from selling products bearing our brands
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or inability of our licensees or franchisees to calculate royalties or generate royalty reports
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Any of these events could severely harm our business, results of operations and prospects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Unanticipated changes in our tax provisions or adverse outcomes resulting from examination of our income tax returns could adversely affect our net income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are subject to income taxes in the United States, California and certain other state jurisdictions. Our effective income tax rates could in the future be adversely affected by changes in tax laws or interpretations of tax laws, or by changes in the valuation of our deferred tax assets and liabilities. Significant judgment is required in determining our provision for income taxes. In the ordinary course of our business, there are many transactions and calculations where the ultimate tax determination is uncertain. We may be audited by tax authorities, which could evaluate and disagree with our judgments regarding our tax provisions. Although we believe our tax estimates are reasonable, the final determination of tax audits and any related litigation could be expensive to defend and materially different from our historical income tax provisions and accruals. The results of an audit or litigation could materially affect our income tax provision, net income or cash flows in the period or periods for which that determination is made. In addition, changes in tax rules&nbsp;may adversely affect our future reported financial results or the way in which we conduct our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Compliance with changing securities laws, regulations and financial reporting standards will increase our costs and pose challenges for our management team.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Existing, changing and new laws, regulations, listing requirements and other standards relating to corporate governance and public disclosure create uncertainty for public companies and significantly increase the costs and risks associated with operating as a publicly traded company in the United States. Our management team devotes significant time and financial resources to comply with existing and evolving standards for public companies. Further, the SEC has passed, promulgated or proposed new rules on a variety of subjects including, for example, with respect to the preparation and filing of financial statements, establishment or disclosure of clawback and hedging policies and disclosure of executive compensation information. The existence of new and proposed laws and regulations relating to our financial reporting or other disclosure obligations or that impose additional or more stringent compliance requirements could make it more difficult for us to attract and retain qualified members of our board of directors (&#x201C;Board of Directors&#x201D;), particularly to serve on our audit and compensation committees, and qualified executive officers. In addition, in order to comply with existing and any new or additional requirements, we may need to add additional accounting staff, engage consultants or change our internal practices, standards and policies, which could significantly increase our costs and divert the time and attention of our management team away from revenue generating activities. Notwithstanding our efforts, it is possible in future periods that our financial and other public reporting may not be considered timely, accurate or complete. If reporting delays or errors actually occur, we could be subject to sanctions or investigation by regulatory authorities, such as the SEC, which could involve fines or other penalties, adversely affect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#CHKE-20160130X10K_HTM_TOC">

	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

</DIV>
