<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Notwithstanding the foregoing, at Landlord&#x2019;s option, in addition to any other remedies available to Landlord under the Lease, as amended hereby, at law and/or in equity, the Extension Option shall not be deemed properly exercised if as of the date of delivery of the Exercise Notice (as defined below) by Tenant, Tenant is in default under the Lease, as amended hereby, beyond any applicable notice and cure periods. Upon the proper exercise of the Extension Option, the Revised Term shall be extended for the Option Term. The Extension Option is personal to the original Tenant executing this Second Amendment (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Original Tenant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and may only be exercised by the Original Tenant (and not any assignee, sublessee or other transferee of Tenant&#x2019;s interest in the Lease, as amended hereby) if the Original Tenant occupies the entire Premises as of the date of Tenant&#x2019;s delivery of the Exercise Notice.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:20PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.2.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Option Rent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The Base Rent payable by Tenant during the Option Term (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Option Rent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shall be equal to the Fair Market Rental Rate for the entire Premises. As used herein, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Fair Market Rental Rate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shall mean the annual base rent at which non-equity renewal tenants, as of the commencement of the Option Term, will be leasing non-sublease, unencumbered renewal space comparable in size, location and quality to the entire Premises for a comparable term as the Option Term, which comparable space is located in the Building and in other comparable first-class office buildings in Van Nuys and Sherman Oaks, California
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Comparable Buildings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;), taking into
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consideration all free rent and other out-of-pocket concessions generally being granted at such time for such comparable space for the Option Term (including, without limitation, any tenant improvement allowance provided for such comparable space, with the amount of such tenant improvement allowance to be provided for the Premises during the Option Term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	be determined after taking into account the age, quality and layout of the tenant improvements in the entire Premises as of the commencement of the Option Term with consideration to the fact that the improvements existing in the Premises are specifically suitable to Tenant).
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:20PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.3.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Exercise of Option
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The Extension Option shall be exercised by Tenant, if at all, only in the following manner: (i)&nbsp;Tenant shall deliver written notice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exercise Notice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to Landlord not more than twelve (12) months nor less than nine (9)&nbsp;months prior to the expiration of the Revised Term stating that Tenant is exercising the Extension Option (with the Option Rent to be determined as provided herein below); and (ii)&nbsp;Landlord, after receipt of Tenant&#x2019;s Exercise Notice, shall deliver written notice (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Option Rent Notice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to Tenant not less than eight (8)&nbsp;months prior to the expiration of the Revised Term setting forth the Option Rent. Within fifteen (15) days after receipt of the Option Rent Notice, Tenant shall notify Landlord in writing whether Tenant accepts or disagrees with the Fair Market Rental Rate set forth in the Option Rent Notice (if Tenant fails to deliver such written notice, Tenant shall
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	deemed to have accepted the Fair Market Rental Rate set forth in the Option Rent Notice). Should Tenant accept (or be deemed to have accepted) the Fair Market Rental Rate set forth in the Option Rent Notice, the Option Rent for the Option Term shall be as set forth in the Option Rent Notice and the following provisions of Section&nbsp;5.4 below shall not apply. Should Tenant properly and timely disagree with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fair
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Market Rental Rate set forth in the Option Rent Notice, such Fair Market Rental Rate shall be determined pursuant to Section&nbsp;5.4 below. Tenant&#x2019;s failure to deliver the Exercise Notice on or before the delivery date therefor specified hereinabove, shall be deemed to constitute Tenant&#x2019;s waiver of the Extension Option.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A NAME="CHKE-20160130EX104080911_HTM_PB_3_085213_5796">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:20PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage82"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:20PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.4.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Determination of Option Rent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. If Tenant timely objects to the Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term submitted by Landlord in the Option Rent Notice therefor, Landlord and Tenant shall thereafter attempt in good faith to agree upon such Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term, using their best good faith efforts. If Landlord and Tenant fail to reach agreement on such Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term within fifteen (15) days following Tenant&#x2019;s objection thereto (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Outside Agreement Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	then each party shall submit to the other party a separate written determination of the Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term within ten (10)&nbsp;business days after the Outside Agreement Date, and such determinations shall be submitted to arbitration in accordance with the provisions of Sections 5.4 (a)&nbsp;through (g)&nbsp;below. The failure of Tenant or Landlord to submit a written determination of the Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term within such ten (10)&nbsp;business day period shall conclusively be deemed to be such party&#x2019;s approval of the Fair Market Rental
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Rate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for the Option Term submitted within such ten (10)&nbsp;business day period by the other party.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Landlord and Tenant shall each appoint one (1)&nbsp;&#x201C;appraiser&#x201D; who shall by profession be a real estate broker who shall have been active over the ten (10)&nbsp;year period ending on the date of such appointment in the leasing of the Building and the Comparable Buildings. The determination of the appraisers shall be limited solely to the issue of whether Landlord&#x2019;s or Tenant&#x2019;s submitted Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term is the closer to the actual Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term as determined by the appraisers, taking into account the requirements with respect thereto set forth in Section&nbsp;5.2 above. Each such appraiser shall be appointed within fifteen (15) days after the Outside Agreement Date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	two (2)&nbsp;appraisers so appointed shall, within fifteen (15) days of the date of the appointment of the last appointed appraiser, agree upon and appoint a third appraiser who shall be qualified under the same criteria set forth hereinabove for qualification of the initial two (2)&nbsp;appraisers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The three (3)&nbsp;appraisers shall, within thirty (30) days of the appointment of the third appraiser, reach a decision as to which of Landlord&#x2019;s or Tenant&#x2019;s submitted Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term is closer to the actual Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term and shall select such closer determination as the Fair Market Rental Rate for the Option Term and notify Landlord and Tenant thereof.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The decision of the majority of the three (3)&nbsp;appraisers shall be binding upon Landlord and Tenant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If either Landlord or Tenant fails to appoint an appraiser within the time period specified in Section&nbsp;5.4(a)&nbsp;above, the appraiser appointed by one of them shall reach the decision described in Section&nbsp;5.4(c)&nbsp;above, notify Landlord and Tenant thereof, and such appraiser&#x2019;s decision shall be binding upon Landlord and Tenant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(f)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the two (2)&nbsp;appraisers fail to agree upon and appoint a third appraiser, a third appraiser shall be appointed by the Superior Court in and for Los Angeles County.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A NAME="CHKE-20160130EX104080911_HTM_PB_4_085328_2897">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage83"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(g)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Each party shall pay the fees and expenses of the appraiser appointed by or on behalf of it, and each shall pay one-half of the fees and expenses of the third appraiser, if any.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:27PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Right of First Offer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. During the period (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	F
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	irst Offer Period
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	from and after the Revised Commencement Date until the last day of the month which is twenty-four (24) months after the Revised Commencement Date (subject, however, to the limitations set forth below in this Section&nbsp;6), Tenant shall have a one-time right of first offer to lease approximately 4,455 rentable square feet of space, commonly known as Suite&nbsp;650, located on the sixth (6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;">
	th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) floor of the Building, as depicted on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Exhibit&nbsp;A-1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	attached hereto (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	First Offer Space
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;), when the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	First Offer Space becomes Available for Lease (as defined and provided hereinbelow) as determined by Landlord. For purposes hereof, the First Offer Space shall become
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Available for Lease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	when (i)&nbsp;Landlord is willing to give to, or accept from, any third party (excluding existing tenants of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	First
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Offer Space, holders of Superior Rights [as hereinafter defined], affiliates of any such existing tenants of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	First Offer Space, or affiliates of holders of such Superior Rights), a bona fide proposal to lease all or any portion of the First Offer Space, and (ii)&nbsp;any lease pertaining to the First Offer Space as of the Revised Commencement Date has expired or otherwise terminated (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Initial Third Party Lease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	) &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(for purposes of clarification, Landlord shall have the right, without offering the First Offer Space to Tenant pursuant to the provisions of this Section&nbsp;6, to renew or extend the Initial Third Party Lease, whether or not such renewal or extension is pursuant to an express written provision in such Initial Third Party Lease, and regardless of whether such renewal or extension is consummated pursuant to a lease amendment or a new lease). Notwithstanding anything in this Section&nbsp;6 to the contrary, Tenant&#x2019;s right of first offer set forth herein shall he subject and subordinate to all rights of expansion, renewal, extension, first refusal, first offer or similar rights for all or any portion of the First Offer Space granted to any tenants of the Building pursuant to leases which have been executed as of the Revised Commencement Date and any Initial Third Party Lease (collectively, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Superior Rights
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;).
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:20PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6.1.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Terms of Lease of First Offer Space
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Landlord shall give Tenant written notice (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	First Offer Notice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that the First Offer Space is Available for Lease by Tenant as provided above (as such availability is determined by Landlord) pursuant to the terms of Tenant&#x2019;s right of first offer, as set forth in this Section&nbsp;6, provided that no holder of Superior Rights desires to lease all or any portion of such First Offer Space. Any such Landlord&#x2019;s First Offer Notice delivered by Landlord in accordance with the provisions of Section&nbsp;6 above shall identify and describe the First Offer Space and set forth the material, economic terms upon which Landlord would lease the First Offer Space to a third party pursuant to such bona fide proposal described in Section&nbsp;6(i)&nbsp;above (collectively, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Economic Terms
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which Economic Terms shall include, without limitation: (i)&nbsp;the anticipated commencement date for the First Offer Space; (ii)&nbsp;the tenant improvements and/or tenant improvement allowance to be provided by Landlord, if any, for the First Offer Space, and a schedule of construction of such tenant improvements for the First Offer Space, if any (and/or whether the First Offer Space will be delivered &#x201C;AS IS&#x201D;); (iii)&nbsp;the Base Rent payable for the First Offer Space; and (iv)&nbsp;the term of the lease for the First Offer Space, which shall in all events be coterminous with the Revised Term notwithstanding the lease term intended to be offered by Landlord to such third party; provided, however, if the lease term for such third party lease proposal is different than such coterminous term, then the Economic Terms as provided to Tenant in Landlord&#x2019;s First Offer Notice shall be
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	adjusted and pro-rated by Landlord as reasonably appropriate taking into account such coterminous term. In addition, Landlord&#x2019;s First Offer Notice shall also include an option (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Suite&nbsp;210 Termination Option
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for Tenant to elect to terminate the Lease (as amended hereby) with respect to the Suite&nbsp;210 Premises only, which Suite&nbsp;210 Termination Option may be exercised by Tenant in Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice (as defined below) only if Tenant elects to lease the entire First Offer Space pursuant to Section&nbsp;6.2(i)&nbsp;below, whereby the Lease shall terminate with respect to the Suite&nbsp;210 Premises, only, effective as of day immediately prior to the commencement of the term of the lease for the First Offer Space (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Suite&nbsp;210 Surrender Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;).
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:20PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6.2.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Procedure for Acceptance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. On or before the date which is five (5) business days after Tenant&#x2019;s receipt of the Landlord&#x2019;s First Offer Notice (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Election Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Tenant shall deliver written notice to Landlord
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	pursuant to which Tenant shall have the one-time right to elect either to: (i)&nbsp;lease the entire First Offer Space identified in the First Offer Notice upon the Economic Terms set forth in the First Offer Notice and the same non-Economic Terms as set forth in the Lease, as hereby amended; or (ii)&nbsp;not lease the First Offer Space identified in the First Offer Notice. Further, in the event that Tenant elects clause (i)&nbsp;above, Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice shall also provide whether or not Tenant elects to exercise the Suite&nbsp;210 Termination Option. If Tenant does not deliver Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice electing one of the options set forth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	clauses (i)&nbsp;or (ii)&nbsp;hereinabove by the Election Date, then Tenant shall be deemed to have elected not to lease the First Offer Space or to exercise the Suite&nbsp;210 Termination Option. If Tenant elects or is deemed to have elected not to lease the First Offer Space, then Tenant&#x2019;s right of first offer set forth in this Section&nbsp;14 shall terminate and Landlord shall thereafter have the right to lease all or any portion of the First Offer Space to anyone to whom Landlord desires on any terms Landlord desires. Furthermore, the Suite&nbsp;210 Termination Option shall be void, and the Lease, as hereby amended, shall continue in full force and effect with respect to the entire Premises. If Tenant timely delivers Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice to Landlord on or before the Election Date in accordance with clause (i)&nbsp;hereinabove, then Tenant shall lease the First Offer Space upon the Economic Terms contained therein and the non-Economic Terms set forth in the Lease, as hereby amended. In addition, if Tenant timely delivers Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice to Landlord on or before the Election Date in accordance with clause (i)&nbsp;hereinabove, and Tenant shall have properly exercised the Suite&nbsp;210 Termination Option in Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice, then the Lease, as hereby amended, shall terminate with respect to the Suite&nbsp;210 Premises only, as of the Suite&nbsp;210 Surrender Date, whereby Tenant shall vacate and deliver exclusive possession of the Suite&nbsp;210 Premises to Landlord on or prior to the Suite&nbsp;210 Surrender Date in accordance with the applicable provisions of the Lease. Notwithstanding the foregoing provisions of this Section&nbsp;6 to the contrary, at Landlord&#x2019;s option and in addition to any and all remedies available to Landlord, the Suite&nbsp;210 Termination Option shall not be deemed to be properly exercised if as of the date Tenant delivers to Landlord Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice exercising the Suite&nbsp;210 Termination Option, Tenant is in default under the Lease, as amended hereby, beyond all applicable notice and cure periods. Notwithstanding anything in this Section&nbsp;6 to the contrary, Tenant must elect to exercise its right of first offer herein with respect to the entire First Offer Space identified in Landlord&#x2019;s First Offer Notice and may not elect to lease only a portion thereof.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Default; Personal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Notwithstanding anything in this Section&nbsp;6 above to the contrary, at Landlord&#x2019;s option, and in addition to all of Landlord&#x2019;s remedies under the Lease, as hereby amended, at law or in equity, the right of first offer hereinabove granted to Tenant with respect to the First Offer Space shall not be deemed to be properly exercised if, as of the date Tenant delivers Tenant&#x2019;s Election Notice to Landlord for the First Offer Space, Tenant has previously been in default under the Lease (as hereby amended) beyond the expiration of all applicable notice and cure periods. In addition, Tenant&#x2019;s right of first offer to lease the First Offer Space is personal to the Original Tenant, and may not be assigned or exercised, voluntarily or involuntarily, by or to, any person or entity other than the Original Tenant, and shall only be available to and exercisable by the Original Tenant, when the Original Tenant is in actual and physical possession of the entire Premises then leased by Tenant under the Lease, as hereby amended.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Brokers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Landlord and Tenant each hereby represents and warrants to the other party that it has had no dealings with any real estate broker or agent in connection with the negotiation of this Second Amendment, other than Colliers International, representing Landlord (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Broker
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and that it knows of no real estate broker or agent (other than the Broker) who is entitled to a commission in connection with this Second Amendment. Landlord shall pay the brokerage commissions owing to the Broker in connection with this Second Amendment pursuant to the terms of a separate written agreement between Landlord and the Broker. Each party agrees to indemnify and defend the other party against and hold the other party harmless from any and all claims, demands, losses, liabilities, lawsuits, judgments, and costs and expenses (including, without limitation, reasonable attorneys&#x2019; fees) with respect to any leasing commission or equivalent compensation alleged to be owing on account of any breach of the foregoing representation and warranty by the indemnifying party in connection with this Second Amendment.
</FONT>
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	I, Jason Boling, certify that:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 30PT 0PT 0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;K of Cherokee&nbsp;Inc.;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 30PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 30PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 30PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The registrant&#x2019;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;15(e) and 15d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;15(f) and 15d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;15(f)) for the registrant and have:

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	5.
